Procedure of Using Cloud to Depth Conversion Node
===================================================

As a process node, the usage of this node is very simple:
* Convert point cloud to depth image
* Convert depth image back to point cloud

Convert point cloud to depth image
------------------------------------

Select conversion type to be "Cloud to Depth". Set the cloud link correctly.

.. image:: ../../_static/images/3d_process/cloud_to_depth/cloud_to_depth_config.PNG
   :width: 100%

If the "Adjust Box" option is checked in display, adjust bouding box in the display to select which part of the point cloud will be converted to the depth image.

.. image:: ../../_static/images/3d_process/cloud_to_depth/adjust_box.PNG
   :width: 100%

If you notice some wierd grids in the depth image, reduce the width and height of the depth image.

.. image:: ../../_static/images/3d_process/cloud_to_depth/size_too_large.PNG
   :width: 100%

Convert depth image back to point cloud
------------------------------------------

This functionality only works if the depth map is obtained by cloud to depth conversion node. Otherwise, the point cloud will be created using default camera intrinsics.

.. image:: ../../_static/images/3d_process/cloud_to_depth/depth_to_cloud_config.PNG
   :width: 100%
